fields.value: Representation in the America's Legislature Project

dsDescriptionValue.value:
***PLEASE NOTE ALL DATA ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE. AN OFFICIAL ANNOUNCEMENT WILL BE MADE WHEN THE DATA ARE COMPLETE***

This is a project supported by the National Science Foundation (SES-0094635 and SES-0242571) and at Indiana University, the College of Arts and Science and the Office of the Vice President for Research.

The principal investigator of this project is Professor Gerald C. Wright, and the research was conducted at Indiana University. On this website you will find links to the roll call data we have currently available and upcoming data releases. This page functions as t he primary source for obtaining the data and will be routinely updated throughout the summer as we post the first round of the data collection. Please check back for updates.

If you use this data please include the following citation: Gerald Wright. 2004. "Representation in America's Legislatures." Indiana University: National Science Foundation Grant.

All of the data on this dataverse is available for download at no charge. We would like to know how our data is being used, to that end we would appreciate receiving a copy of any papers using this data. Please send a Microsoft Word or pdf version of any papers you write using the data to: Jerry Wright.

publicationCitation.value:
Papers presented using RAL data:

Gerald Wright, Tracy Osborn. 2002. "Party and Roll Call Voting in the American Legislature" Midwest Political Science Association, Chicago: April 25-28. article available here

Gerald Wright, Jon Winburn. 2002. "Patterns of Constituency-Legislator Policy Congruence in the States" Second Annual Conference on State Politics and Policy, Milwaukee: May 24-25. article available here

Gerald Wright, Jon Winburn. 2003. "The Effects of Size and Party on the Dimensionality of Roll Calls" Third Annual Conference on State Politics and Policy, Tucson, AZ: March 14-15 and Midwest Political Science Association, Chicago: April 3-5. article available here

Gerald Wright, Tracy Osborn, Jon Winburn. 2004. "Parties and Representation in the American Legislatures." Midwest Political Science Association, Chicago: April 15-18. article available here
